quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  16,1,"Allah’s edict is coming! So do not seek to hasten it. Immaculate is He and exalted above [having] any partners that they ascribe [to Him]"
  16,2,"He sends down the angels with the spirit of His command to whomever He wishes of His servants: ‘Warn [the people] that there is no god except Me; so be wary of Me.’"
  16,3,"He created the heavens and the earth with consummate wisdom. He is above having any partners that they ascribe [to Him]"
  16,4,"He created man from a drop of [seminal] fluid, and, behold, he is an open contender"
  16,5,"He created the cattle, in which there is warmth for you and [other] uses, and some of them you eat"
  16,6,There is in them a beauty for you when you bring them home for rest and when you drive them forth to pasture
  16,7,"And they bear your burdens to towns, which you could not reach except by straining yourselves. Indeed your Lord is most kind and merciful"
  16,8,"And horses, mules and asses, for you to ride them, and for pomp, and He creates what you do not know"
  16,9,"With Allah rests guidance to the straight path, and some of the paths are devious, and had He wished He would have guided you all"